The paper deals with graph problems in hyperbolic space, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus is on algorithmic solutions for various graph problems, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.IT). Finally, the paper introduces new separator theorems, which is a technique used in structural graph theory (cs.SI).
